comments.undefined:
This ontology offers vocabularies for representing activities of daily living (ADL) that can be run in the VirtualHome (http://virtual-home.org/), run-time home situations, objects, and relationships among them.
This ontology is an extended version of the HomeOntology (https://github.com/valexande/HomeOntology).

edge <object1, close, object2> denotes that the distance between center of object1 (object2) to the bounding box of object2 (object1) is < 1.5 units (~meters)

A target object of an event.
If an agent pours milk into a glass, the value of the value of the targetObject is the glass.
analogue of holds_rh for left hand

there is an edge <object1, facing, object2> if object2 is lookable, is visible from object1, and the distance between the centers is < 5 units (~meters). If object1 is a sofa or a chair it should also be turned towards object2
edge <character, holds_rh, object> is used to indicate that character holds an object in its right hand

A main object of an event.
If an agent pours milk into a glass, the value of the mainObject is the milk.
